<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>PDFUnicorn - online PDF generator</title>
	%= include 'site/head'
	%= include 'mixpanel'
  
    <!-- record main page view -->
  	<script type="text/javascript">mixpanel.track('view-home-page')</script>
</head>

<body>
	%= include 'site/header'

    <div class="container">
        <div class="jumbotron">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12">
                    <p>At it's core, PDFUnicorn is a web service for making PDF files.</p>
                    
                    <p>PDF files can be created directly from source documents, or from data
                    applied to custom templates.</p>
                    
                    <p>The markup language is intentionally simple to allow you to start creating
                    templates and documents as quickly and easily as possible.</p>
                    
                    <p>Document content is securely sent from your server to ours enabling private
                    customer text and images to be included without allowing remote access to your
                    server and content.</p>
                    
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">

                    <p>Document images can be uploaded at print quality resolutions to create the
                    best looking documents possible.</p>
                    
                    <p>This is not a html2pdf conversion service, it is designed as a simple, reliable
                    way to create multi-page documents with content repeated on each page where
                    required.</p>
                    
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-md-6">
                
                  <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="/img/tax_invoice_snap.png"><br />
                  
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="well">
        	<div class="row">
        		<div class="col-md-8">
                    <p class="lead">
                        You can try out creating a pdf by combining JSON data and a PUML template
                        in our online demonstration.
                    </p>
        		</div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <a href="/playground" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Create a PDF now!</a>
                </div>
        	</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="well">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <p class="lead">
                        Using our simple API you can:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Upload your logo and other images at print quality resolutions.</li>
                            <li>Upload your templates which can automatically handle paging and repeated headers.</li>
                            <li>Send your data to our server and get back pixel perfect PDF documents to send to your clients.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p class="lead">
                        Check out the documentation for our
                        <a href="docs/api">API</a> and
                        <a href="docs/markup">markup language</a>.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="signup">
            %= include 'site/signup_prompt'
        </div>
        
        <div class="well">
        	<div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <img src="/img/pdfunicorn_logo_200.png" title="The Unicorn" alt="[logo] The Unicorn">
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-9">
                    <p class="lead">PDFUnicorn is a PDF creation web service for businesses who need to generate custom
                    PDF files on demand. We use a custom HTML-like markup language designed for laying
                    out pageable documents in the simplest way possible.</p>
                </div>
        	</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    %= include 'site/foot'

</body>
</html>
